    "summary": "UX / Product designer with over a decade of experience in the field. Worked independently within agile scrum teams, but also as part of a large design department. I have failed and succeeded, but most importantly, grew and learned a ton. Extensive experience in (B2C & B2B) e-commerce websites and native apps at large corporates. \n\nI love doing the hard work to make it simple. Really digging into the problem, no matter the size and uncovering all the complexity, working towards a scalable solution that might be a redesign, introducing a new component or just a simple change in copy. Whatever gets the job done. Even the smallest iterations offer an opportunity to evolve the platform as a whole.\n\nThorough hands-on experience with creating customer experiences from higher, strategic level, preferably in an iterative process where assumptions are systematically validated. Passionate (maybe a little obsessive at times) about user and their needs and wants, to maintain a healthy balance between adding value for businesses as well as people, while levering (technical) enablers.\n\nI love doing the hard work to make it simple. Focusing on improving customer experiences from high-level, strategic concepts to smaller initiatives, preferably in an iterative process where assumptions are validated. Passionate (a little obsessive at times) about user needs and wants, creating experiences which are enjoyable but also efficient, while aligning user and business goals with (technical) possibilities. If those goals are.\n\nExperience mostly as part of the design department of bol.com and NS (Dutch Railways).",
